snippet: Parliament dismissed Iran’s science minister on Wednesday over his supposed support for pro-Western voices at universities, dealing a blow to moderate President Hassan Rouhani.
abstract: Parliament dismisses Iran's science minister Reza Faraji Dana over his apparent support for pro-Western voices at universities; dismissal deals blow to moderate Pres Hassan Rouhani.
lead_paragraph: Parliament dismissed Iran’s science minister on Wednesday over his supposed support for pro-Western voices at universities, dealing a blow to moderate President Hassan Rouhani.

headline.main: Iran: Minister Seen as Pro-Western Is Ousted in Rebuke to the President
headline.print_headline: Iran: Minister Seen as Pro-Western Is Ousted in Rebuke to the President
